1
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:02,400
Sign it.

2
00:00:02,720 --> 00:00:03,720
Are you Pai?
Yes.

3
00:00:04,960 --> 00:00:06,000
This is unacceptable!

4
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:08,560
The ink on the divorce certificate
hasn’t even begun to dry!

5
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:11,320
Work for Empire.

6
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:13,560
I think it’s best for you to take the offer.

7
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,040
I’ll take it.

8
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:16,880
Go on a date with me.

9
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:19,080
I will agree if you stop making a ruckus.

10
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:23,000
You ever met someone so right for you?

11
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,240
How could our relationship work?

12
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:25,560
How could I forget everything
that happened?

13
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:26,280
You don’t have to forget.

14
00:00:26,680 --> 00:00:29,760
If you have to be mad at me
for the rest of our lives, I’ll be here.

15
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:35,640
Hiking is definitely
going to be the new luxury.

16
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:39,280
I think this can definitely mint money
if we just know how to pitch it.

17
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:42,080
We met on a hike, didn’t we?

18
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:42,960
Right.

19
00:00:46,360 --> 00:00:46,880
Thank you.

20
00:00:48,120 --> 00:00:49,440
You guys should hurry up and leave
if you want to beat the morning traffic.

21
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:51,480
Oh, right, Pai.

22
00:00:52,080 --> 00:00:54,800
Grandpa invited me over for dinner
at home after work.

23
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:55,720
You wanna join us?

24
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:58,680
Who did he invite?

25
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:04,120
Me.

26
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:06,120
But that’s as good as inviting you.

27
00:01:07,160 --> 00:01:08,040
I doubt it is.

28
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,200
Come on.

29
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:16,000
You’ll never make up with him
if you keep sulking.

30
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:17,840
I’m not sulking.

31
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,200
You know how busy this place gets.

32
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,440
I don’t have time for dinner.

33
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:22,600
Just go to work.

34
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,800
Alright.

35
00:01:25,080 --> 00:01:26,400
I’m leaving.

36
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,400
Bye, Pai.
Bye, Tim.

37
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:29,160
Goodbye.

38
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:30,360
Bye, Tim.

39
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,200
Let me carry this.

40
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:43,760
Work?

41
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,320
Oh. Right.

42
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:50,520
I told you I got a job, right?

43
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:54,000
But I’ll have to be at the
client’s office a lot, though.

44
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:58,040
I’ll be busy for a while.

45
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:02,640
That’s perfect.

46
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,720
I could use some peace and quiet.

47
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:11,760
I’ll try to make time for you.

48
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:14,320
And I’ll keep you updated.

49
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,360
Alright?

50
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:17,040
Why would you do that?

51
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:18,320
It’s not like we’re dating, you know?

52
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,920
But last night you said
you wanted me to sta—

53
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:23,560
That didn’t mean I wanted
to get back together.

54
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:26,440
Okay.

55
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,120
Fine by me.

56
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:33,280
I have to go to work, though.

57
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,720
Can I get some emotional support?

58
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:36,880
No.

59
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,200
I’d say yes.
Hey!

60
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:43,640
If you hit me again, I’m kissing you.

61
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:44,520
Alright.

62
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:46,120
Bring it on.

63
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,160
Bring it.
Another shove, huh?

64
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:48,600
Alright.

65
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:50,960
You wanna try that again?

66
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,080
Oh, alright!

67
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:53,840
Fine by me!

68
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:54,520
There!

69
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:03,200
Okay!

70
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:13,360
TWO MONTHS LATER

71
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:15,880
See?

72
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:18,360
I told you it takes less than
10 minutes to set up.

73
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:21,400
With friends, I’d say it can take
as quickly as five minutes.

74
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,240
This is super fun, Mama.

75
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:25,440
Here.

76
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:33,600
I’ll take two.

77
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:35,800
Alright, Auntie.

78
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:39,200
We see a 13% increase
in hiking gear sales, sir.

79
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:42,520
As for children’s toys, it’s a 25% spike.

80
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:46,840
Customers’ satisfaction in the past
two months is much better, sir.

81
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,360
And their managers’ evaluation?

82
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,640
For Mr. North, the comment says,

83
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,080
“He’s always trying to improve himself
without being told.”

84
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,080
For Mr. U, it says,

85
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:02,960
“Thorough attention to details.
A caring staff and colleague

86
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:05,400
who makes working more pleasant.”

87
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:11,200
I think it’s time to start training at the office.

88
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:14,920
I’ll put you two on the same team.

89
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:20,160
You both need to learn how to separate
your personal matters from work.

90
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,560
Thank you, Grandpa.

91
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:24,360
And don’t worry. We can definitely do that.

92
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,440
Am I right, U?

93
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:26,760
Right.

94
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,520
I do believe so.

95
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,840
And you can move back into the condo.

96
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,040
Thank you.

97
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,600
I love you so much, Grandpa.

98
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,360
You’re not mad at me anymore, are you?

99
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:41,760
(Pai?)

100
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:44,320
(U and I passed the first test.)

101
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,880
We’re moving to the sales promotion team.

102
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,560
(We’ll be dining with our team tonight.)

103
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,240
It’s a thank-you dinner, that kind of thing.

104
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,000
You should come.

105
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,280
I can’t.

106
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,040
Pai.

107
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,600
I just want to tell you that…

108
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,320
Grandpa forgave me.

109
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,840
(He gave me back all my credit cards.)

110
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,080
(Should I give you one?)

111
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,000
You don’t have to.

112
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,160
Where are you staying right now?

113
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:17,360
Wanna stay at my place for a while?

114
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:18,960
I can take care of myself.

115
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:23,960
Okay.

116
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:25,800
Oh.
(Hello.)

117
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,800
(Oh, your parents are here.)

118
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:28,640
(Hello.)

119
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:29,720
(I’m on the phone with Pai.)

120
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:30,200
(You are?)
(Yes.)

121
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:33,520
Pai, how are you, love?

122
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,480
(You never come to see your old man.)

123
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:38,440
Oh, we’re busy at the bakery right now.

124
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:39,240
I have to go.

125
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:40,400
Bye.

126
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,320
Oh, honey…

127
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:45,640
What a shame.

128
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,120
I guess he’s busy.

129
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:08,720
Your parents didn’t even try
to help you out or send money?

130
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,000
No.

131
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,240
They have to heed Grandpa’s words.

132
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,200
But you’re their child.

133
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,040
I don’t know.

134
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:22,560
They had never been much help
in the first place,

135
00:07:23,520 --> 00:07:24,760
so to them, it’s just as it always was.

136
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:30,360
But you always get by on your own,

137
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,240
so they never have to worry about you.

138
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,680
Unlike North.

139
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:39,640
That dude is worrisome
whether he’s in a pinch or not.

140
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,640
But it’s nice having you
around the bakery, Pai.

141
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,800
You don’t skip work,
you don’t bother people.

142
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,560
And people don’t seem to dare
mess with you.

143
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,520
You’re definitely worth your salary.

144
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:56,480
I’ll give you an extra 600 baht.

145
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:01,760
Do you know why no one
dares mess with me, Pure?

146
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:06,440
…Right.

147
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,200
I–I have a call.

148
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,080
Excuse me.

149
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:26,880
Our next project is a
new promotional campaign

150
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:29,640
under the slogan “Gifts for Lovers.”

151
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,400
You guys are dating, right?

152
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,240
This must be easy.

153
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,080
You know all about each other.

154
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:39,480
How about we have a little challenge?

155
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:41,920
We’ll split into two teams.

156
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,960
Each will come up with their
own ideas for the campaign.

157
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,680
U, you’re on Team A.

158
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,720
North, you’re on Team B.

159
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:51,920
Of course.

160
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:55,200
How serious is a challenge
like this usually?

161
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,040
Very serious.

162
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,160
There’s a prize.

163
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:58,720
A prize?
That’s right.

164
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:04,280
This new project is a welcome ritual
for our new members.

165
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,560
As for the prize…

166
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:09,400
The winner will pass the probation
right away.

167
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,920
What happens to the person
who doesn’t pass it?

168
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:21,880
I mean, Grandpa wouldn’t fire me.

169
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,760
I believe he plans to put
you back in camping gear.

170
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,560
I won’t go easy on you, U.

171
00:09:58,040 --> 00:10:01,000
“Now that everyone’s busy,
it gets lonely around here.”

172
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:05,120
“Is this what it feels like to be forgotten?”

173
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:07,360
Stop it.

174
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:09,520
That’s not what the voice
in my head is saying.

175
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:12,800
Oh, but Pai,

176
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,480
is Tim working an office job now?

177
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:17,680
I haven’t seen him in a while.

178
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:19,240
I thought he’s a freelancer?

179
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:25,520
He said he had to be at the office because
of some computer program and discretion.

180
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,280
He’s only here a few days a week.

181
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:32,520
I’m sure someone around here must be
missing him like crazy right now.

182
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,440
I don’t.

183
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:35,360
I’m happy he’s not here since
he’s always such a fuss to deal with.

184
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,320
So you don’t miss him?
Not at all!

185
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:42,280
Well, what do these
duckling cookies mean?

186
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,200
It’s just a character.

187
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,040
It doesn't represent anyone.

188
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:51,520
Oh?

189
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:54,240
Tim just sent in an order.

190
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:56,080
He said he needs it delivered to his office.

191
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,960
“I must ask Pai to make the delivery.”

192
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,560
“I miss him.”

193
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,440
Nonsense.

194
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,000
Alright.

195
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,960
I’ll call some delivery guy, then.

196
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:07,880
No.

197
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,040
I’ll go.

198
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,120
Let’s think about cost.

199
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:12,200
Give me the key.

200
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:13,560
Quickly.

201
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,160
Sure.

202
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:18,840
Pai.
Hmm?

203
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,720
Did you forget the food?

204
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,760
Oh, I’m getting it done.

205
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,720
I’ll get it done right now.

206
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,360
You must be in a hurry.

207
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:33,600
That yearning rushes you, doesn’t it?

208
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:34,360
Keep talking.

209
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,040
I won’t!

210
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,680
(You can come in when you’re here.)

211
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:47,720
Hello?

212
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:50,600
Yeah.
It’s here.

213
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:52,920
I found it.
It’s on the table.

214
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,080
You said it was in a folder.

215
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:58,120
You idiot, I was looking everywhere for it.

216
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,400
You guys gonna be here soon?

217
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:01,560
Right.

218
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:02,840
I’ll call you back.

219
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:10,840
Wanna come in?

220
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:12,520
No, thanks.

221
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,720
You should get back to work.
I don’t want to bother you.

222
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:15,960
It’s more than alright.

223
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,000
Just come on in.

224
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,400
Why did you even let me in here?

225
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:25,920
It’s okay.

226
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:27,760
What? It’s alright.

227
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:29,000
Give it here.
I’ll get it.

228
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:31,320
Hold on.

229
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,360
This… I made this for you.

230
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:41,760
You did?

231
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:43,400
What is it?

232
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:47,720
Cookies?

233
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,360
Adorable.

234
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:55,240
You’re just my test subject
in case this isn’t edible.

235
00:12:58,680 --> 00:12:59,480
Did you name it?

236
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,840
You try it and name it.

237
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:05,400
Oh, I don’t think I can take a bite.

238
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:06,560
Look at it.

239
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,280
It’s so adorable I don’t think
I have the heart to eat it.

240
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:10,240
Just give it back here if you don’t like it.
Hey.

241
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:11,800
I like it.

242
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:14,000
I’m just saying it’s too cute to eat.

243
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,080
Just eat.

244
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:16,480
No.

245
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:19,480
Here.

246
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:20,840
I’ll make more.

247
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:30,600
It’s good.

248
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:35,000
But… it smells familiar.

249
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,200
I knew you liked lemon
so I put it in as well.

250
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,000
Any ideas about the name?

251
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:48,160
How about IMY and ILY?

252
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:48,640
What?

253
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:52,640
It’s short for “I miss you” and “I love you.”

254
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:53,720
No.

255
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,200
That’s not adorable at all.

256
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:58,480
What about Immy and Illy?

257
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,960
“Hello. My name is Immy.”

258
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:03,400
“I’m also Illy.”

259
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:06,600
“Nice to meet you, Pai.”

260
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,600
“Please don’t eat me.”

261
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:09,280
Stop it.

262
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:10,760
Take it back.

263
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:12,880
You’re so unimaginative.

264
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,400
Ahem!

265
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,880
I’ve never felt more single in my life.

266
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,320
I probably should go.

267
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:21,720
You should not.
Stay.

268
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:23,440
No way.
You’re at work.

269
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:25,200
I’m an outsider.

270
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:26,560
“Outsider”?

271
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:27,720
Don’t you say that again.

272
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,040
He’s right.

273
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,600
Please make yourself at home, Pai.

274
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,600
You know me?

275
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,120
Of course I do.

276
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:42,280
Hey! You can’t use that as your desktop.

277
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:43,160
People could see!

278
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:45,440
What’s with that?

279
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,240
Don’t worry about us.

280
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:50,040
Tim talks about you every day.

281
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:52,200
I feel like we’re friends already.

282
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:53,440
Stop it, all of you.

283
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,720
You’re selling me out.

284
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,320
I doubt it.

285
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,400
We’re just making fun of you.
Make yourself comfortable.

286
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,960
“Lil Immy wants to be eaten.”

287
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:09,800
“Ah!”

288
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:17,920
This is so nice.

289
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:21,960
We work and take breaks
at the same time.

290
00:15:22,520 --> 00:15:23,840
I can be clingy any time I want.

291
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:26,680
Ahem!

292
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:27,960
Oh, dear.

293
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:33,640
You two are just like Mr. Pai and Mr. Tim
when they were going out.

294
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,320
Really?

295
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:39,360
I thought Pai would be
more composed at work.

296
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:42,400
He let it slip sometimes
when I forgot to knock on the door.

297
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:45,240
I can imagine that.

298
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:47,480
How’s your first day at work?

299
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,640
Amazing.

300
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:49,760
Everyone on the team is so nice.

301
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:50,320
It’s been fun.

302
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:53,240
That’s a relief.

303
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:57,000
Did you know a couple on your team literally just broke up last week?

304
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:04,200
The tension in the meeting room
was insane after that.

305
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:07,480
Why did they break up?

306
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,240
Because they worked together.

307
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:16,000
They quit, though, so everyone
can breathe now.

308
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:18,280
Quit?

309
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:18,880
Yes.

310
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,440
Both of them.

311
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:21,760
Both of them?

312
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:24,080
That’s why we had two empty chairs
for you both to fill.

313
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:25,760
Oh, we’re filling in!

314
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:36,960
But I believe you two love each other
enough to not fight over work.

315
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,400
I have to get back to work now.

316
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:41,840
Right.

317
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,240
So we replaced them, huh?

318
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,280
Alright, guys.

319
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:52,240
I think there should be an event for
couples to exchange gifts as a contest.

320
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:53,400
Make it viral.

321
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:59,040
The audience will get to see
the products we’ll put up for display.

322
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:00,720
Yes?

323
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:05,320
Wouldn’t that be too activity-focused?

324
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,800
It wouldn’t help with sales.

325
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:10,000
How about this?

326
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,600
We give some discounts
for paired up products?

327
00:17:13,080 --> 00:17:14,280
Make it cheaper to buy
two products together.

328
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:18,440
I think that seems like the best option
for what we’re aiming to do.

329
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:21,680
But everyone is doing that.

330
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:22,960
We’re looking to hold an event.

331
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,200
We have to do something special.

332
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:27,360
But you can’t be too focused on the event
that you forget to boost sales.

333
00:17:27,360 --> 00:17:29,200
Did you listen to what I said at all?

334
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:31,920
Of course, I did.

335
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,920
I was listening.
That’s why I raised the question.

336
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:38,400
But your idea is something that can
work with even online shopping.

337
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:43,080
But your idea depends on things
going viral, which is too much risk for us.

338
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:46,520
Are you saying my idea is bad?

339
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:48,200
That’s not what I mean.

340
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,480
That’s exactly what you mean!

341
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,680
It just needs more thoughts.

342
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,480
I don’t think it always works out.

343
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:02,480
If your plan is to break them up,
I think it’s working, Papa.

344
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:04,320
It’s not.

345
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:08,640
I wanted them to work together so
they could become life long partners.

346
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:17,680
Where is Tim?

347
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:19,880
He’s still at work.

348
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:21,840
I see.

349
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:28,400
Uhh, is everything okay between you two?

350
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:29,640
- No.
- Yes.

351
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,360
Is it about work?

352
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:39,320
It’s nothing, Pai.

353
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:41,120
It just seems that I’m incapable of
coming up with good ideas.

354
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:43,400
North.

355
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,440
You can’t sulk because of
that comment I made at work.

356
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,600
Oh, sure.

357
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,280
I’m a loser and also a sulker.

358
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:52,520
My bad.

359
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,560
I’m a bad boyfriend and a bad colleague.

360
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:56,680
What?
North.

361
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:01,760
Just go.

362
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:03,640
Bye.

363
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,440
Here we are.

364
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:13,840
Oh, where did they all go?

365
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:15,560
I’ll take all of that.

366
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:17,840
Sure.

367
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:45,920
I’m gonna go.
I can’t anymore.

368
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:47,440
I’m too tired.

369
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:54,800
Hello, Pai?

370
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,280
(It’s nothing. Bye.)

371
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:01,400
Hold on.

372
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:03,680
What’s the matter?

373
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:06,320
(It’s nothing.)

374
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:08,800
Just stay put. I’ll be there.

375
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:10,880
I have to go.

376
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:12,520
See you.

377
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:17,480
Here.

378
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:23,440
You can go home.

379
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:26,080
I just needed someone to open the bottle.

380
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:30,560
What’s wrong?

381
00:21:32,360 --> 00:21:33,120
You can talk to me, you know?

382
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:38,600
I don’t know.

383
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:44,400
Everything that used to be easy suddenly
becomes harder when I’m alone.

384
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:53,960
All this time, I thought I’d done everything all by myself, without anyone’s help.

385
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,400
But now that I’m left behind,

386
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:01,240
it just hurts more than I thought.

387
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:05,920
Pai.

388
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:09,560
Am I such an awful person
that no one wants to stay with me?

389
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:14,000
Pai.

390
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:16,640
No one hates you.

391
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,120
They just don’t know if you need them.

392
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:23,440
I don’t know.

393
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:26,720
No one ever made me feel
that way except…

394
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:32,160
Except who?

395
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:36,760
No.

396
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:38,920
No one.

397
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:45,240
Why are you smiling?

398
00:22:46,840 --> 00:22:47,400
Nothing.

399
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:51,600
I just never thought I’d get to see
this side of you again.

400
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,640
Sorry it makes me happy.

401
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:56,400
This side of me?

402
00:22:57,680 --> 00:23:03,880
Well, the side that gets scared and…

403
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:04,800
makes you think you’re unlovable.

404
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:08,360
Aside from me, I don’t think anyone
has ever seen you like this.

405
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:16,880
Honestly…

406
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:20,160
Why do you even like me?

407
00:23:22,120 --> 00:23:23,160
Why this question all of a sudden?

408
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,200
Because I don’t have an answer
for that question myself.

409
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:40,400
to think that no one loves me.

410
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:42,720
It is so much easier

411
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:46,200
Pai.

412
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,520
They love you.

413
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:56,160
You can call me a liar on anything.

414
00:23:58,040 --> 00:23:59,400
But at least believe me when I tell you this.

415
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,720
Ugh, this is awful.

416
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:33,680
I don’t want to fight.

417
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,480
We get to work together as a couple.

418
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:36,840
I don’t want to break up!

419
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:37,400
What?

420
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:38,680
Break up?

421
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:39,720
Ain’t no way!

422
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:45,400
Come here.

423
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:57,040
I’m sorry I made you feel bad.

424
00:25:01,120 --> 00:25:02,600
I’m sorry as well.

425
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:05,840
Come to think of it,

426
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:08,320
you were right.

427
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:14,200
Should we work together
instead of competing?

428
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:14,840
Here.

429
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:20,440
When you bought me this guy,
why did you decide to buy it then?

430
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:21,640
Why not wait for an occasion?

431
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:24,120
Hmm…

432
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:28,800
When I want someone I love to be happy,

433
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:31,040
I just want it to happen
as soon as possible.

434
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:32,920
The sooner the better.

435
00:25:36,360 --> 00:25:39,160
This campaign is called “Now is the Best.”

436
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:44,120
Most people believe they need special
occasions to buy their loved ones a gift.

437
00:25:44,120 --> 00:25:48,600
But what we’re doing is urging people
to buy them right now.

438
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:56,320
Then let’s try this campaign right now.

439
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:58,560
U!
Yes!

440
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,080
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

441
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:14,880
Pai, dear.

442
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,640
Papa? Mama?

443
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:22,560
What are you doing here?

444
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:26,120
Pure called us.

445
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:27,640
Pure?

446
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:29,360
Yes.

447
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:35,960
He told us you want to talk to Grandpa,
but you don’t know how.

448
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:38,280
Let’s go, Pai.

449
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,800
Life must have gotten too difficult to bear

450
00:26:58,840 --> 00:27:00,240
for you to crawl your way back here.

451
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:02,160
Not at all.

452
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:04,160
I can get by just fine.

453
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,640
Just say what you’re here to say.

454
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:08,160
I don’t have all day.

455
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:19,920
Why do I need a reason to see you?

456
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:24,200
Am I just a former employee
rather than your grandson

457
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:27,240
that you have no reason to talk to
now that he’s quit your company?

458
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:32,200
Did you know that
we never made small talk?

459
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,600
Every time you called me,
it was either about work…

460
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:39,480
Or about North.

461
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:47,560
Do you all even think of me as your family?

462
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:51,240
Don’t you feel anything for losing me?

463
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:56,680
And why are my mistakes always
much bigger than everyone else’s?

464
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,160
That scam hurt me more than anyone.

465
00:28:04,280 --> 00:28:04,840
That day,

466
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:08,680
all you asked me was how I was
going to take responsibility for it.

467
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:13,240
You didn’t even care how I felt.

468
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:42,200
It was me.

469
00:28:44,720 --> 00:28:46,400
I forbid everyone from reaching out to you.

470
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:58,920
Your Papa and Mama pleaded for you
every single day.

471
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,440
I must admit I forgot…

472
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:14,560
that you’re just a child as well.

473
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:31,880
I was angry

474
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:37,520
because I didn’t think you would
make such a big mistake.

475
00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:46,600
I cast you away, knowing full well
you’d make it on your own.

476
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,760
But still, in your worst moment,

477
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:55,480
I abandoned you.

478
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:07,280
I’m sorry.

479
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:21,880
Will you forgive me?

480
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:25,000
I will, Grandpa.

481
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,040
Pai!

482
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:51,000
Are you moving back into your place, Pai?

483
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:51,920
Yes.

484
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:55,760
Will you come back to work
for Empire as well?

485
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:57,920
I’m not sure about that right now.

486
00:30:58,720 --> 00:31:02,160
I still have to work at the bakery
until I find someone to replace me.

487
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:05,920
I told you Pure called us.

488
00:31:06,120 --> 00:31:09,480
But Pure confessed
Tim made him make that call.

489
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:31,800
Did you finally make up with your family

490
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:34,360
or did you steal someone’s car?

491
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,040
Both.

492
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:41,640
Should I make dinner
and draw a bath for you tonight?

493
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:42,880
No.

494
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,240
It’s been a good day.

495
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:48,200
Hey.

496
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,800
I was told you forced Pure’s hand.

497
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:56,680
I just thought your parents wouldn’t
listen to me if I called them myself.

498
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,680
You poked your nose
where it doesn’t belong.

499
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:04,440
Who’d be able to stand
seeing someone so miserable?

500
00:32:07,040 --> 00:32:08,040
But you didn’t have to do anything.

501
00:32:08,880 --> 00:32:09,720
I’d feel better on my own.

502
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:11,680
You know,

503
00:32:13,480 --> 00:32:15,640
I used to think you were heartless.

504
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:22,080
But when I saw you cry that day,
I just knew that wasn’t the case.

505
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:25,640
When someone as strong as you gets vulnerable like that in front of their eyes,

506
00:32:27,080 --> 00:32:28,360
no one can keep being mad at him.

507
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,720
Why are you suddenly saying all this?

508
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:38,800
You’re not planning to run off
somewhere now, are you?

509
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,960
Did Grandpa say he’d forgive everything
if you left me alone?

510
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:52,160
If that was the case, what would you do?

511
00:32:52,520 --> 00:32:53,120
I would…

512
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:54,800
You would what?

513
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:58,760
I would be happy.

514
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:02,440
Umm.

515
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:04,320
Congratulations, then.

516
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:08,080
That’s exactly what I’m planning to do.

517
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:09,560
No!

518
00:33:16,680 --> 00:33:17,360
I’m kidding.

519
00:33:18,360 --> 00:33:19,560
Who’d be able to do that?

520
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:21,120
Hey.

521
00:33:21,920 --> 00:33:22,800
Are you fooling me again?

522
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:24,360
I’m not.

523
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:26,120
I’m just teasing.

524
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:27,160
Same difference.

525
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:32,440
How can I leave my boyfriend
when he’s so adorable?

526
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:35,840
That’s ‘ex-boyfriend’ to you.

527
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,040
Fine by me.

528
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:43,320
Come in before it starts raining.

529
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:52,960
You should stay until the rain lets up.

530
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:55,600
Driving in this storm is too dangerous.

531
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:07,520
What perfect weather.

532
00:34:08,680 --> 00:34:09,760
If there was a blackout,
it would be almost too cliché.

533
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:25,360
I was waiting for you
to come here tonight.

534
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:28,520
And you did.

535
00:34:30,080 --> 00:34:30,880
How’d you know I’d come?

536
00:34:33,200 --> 00:34:34,520
Well…

537
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,480
When something weighs on your mind,

538
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:38,960
I’m always the one you run to.

539
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:45,880
I’d love to stop doing that.

540
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:48,960
You don’t have to.

541
00:34:50,080 --> 00:34:51,840
I’m here if you ever need me.

542
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:54,680
You don’t give me a break at all, do you?

543
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,240
I like you.

544
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,520
What is there to like?

545
00:35:07,640 --> 00:35:09,160
I didn’t give you an answer.

546
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:14,880
I like you because
you’re good at everything.

547
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:19,640
You get stubborn at times,
and sometimes a little sensitive,

548
00:35:20,680 --> 00:35:22,200
but you’re a romantic person.

549
00:35:24,120 --> 00:35:26,200
When you love someone,
you really care for them.

550
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:39,560
Who wouldn’t fall in love
with such a lovable soul?

551
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:35,040
Pai.

552
00:36:36,080 --> 00:36:36,920
Pai.

553
00:36:37,560 --> 00:36:39,680
Wanna go to work together?

554
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:42,680
Pai!

555
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:44,400
- North.
- P—

556
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:46,200
What’s the matter?

557
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:49,440
Oh, I was gonna ask if you want
to go to work together.

558
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:52,680
But…

559
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:54,720
Whose clothes are these?

560
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:56,280
They look familiar.

561
00:36:56,560 --> 00:37:01,240
Oh, I… stopped by to see Tim last night
and it happened to rain all night.

562
00:37:01,240 --> 00:37:03,080
So I thought it was better to stay over.

563
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:05,280
Stop it.

564
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:06,440
There was nothing going on.

565
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:08,080
I didn’t say anything.

566
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:09,680
Your face already did.

567
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:14,000
Do you want to get changed first?

568
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:17,600
Or are you planning to use this opportunity
to mark your territory?

569
00:37:18,160 --> 00:37:18,920
Of course I’ll change.

570
00:37:19,920 --> 00:37:22,760
But I have to be at the bakery today.

571
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:24,320
I can’t just leave like that.

572
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:25,640
Alright.

573
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:27,640
We can still go to work together.

574
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,920
I’ll drop you off at the bakery
on my way to work.

575
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:32,480
What?

576
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:35,320
What?

577
00:37:36,080 --> 00:37:38,840
Why do you insist on us going
to work together today?

578
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:44,000
It’s…

579
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:46,640
It’s just how I want to show my affection.

580
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,280
My love language, you know?

581
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:52,880
Okay.

582
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:58,560
Oh, right.

583
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:02,080
They’re having the event U and I
came up with today at the mall.

584
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:05,320
You should totally take Tim there.

585
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:06,640
It’s for couples.

586
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:08,240
Get away from me.

587
00:38:08,240 --> 00:38:10,640
Come on. I was wracking
my brain for that campaign!

588
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:18,680
Well done, North.

589
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:31,000
Finally the day is over.

590
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:35,720
I thought it would be more tiring.

591
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:41,200
Adulting, going to work, and…

592
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:44,560
Feeling drained, you know?

593
00:38:46,240 --> 00:38:46,680
You did well.

594
00:38:48,120 --> 00:38:49,840
You work and take care of your family.

595
00:38:50,320 --> 00:38:51,120
You’re all grown up, alright.

596
00:38:57,040 --> 00:38:59,280
But did I take care of you properly?

597
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,040
We spent all day together.

598
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:08,720
But when I work, I focus on work.

599
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:12,680
When I’m with Pai, I focus on Pai.

600
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,840
I didn’t make time for you today.

601
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:18,320
Oh, it’s alright.

602
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:19,080
I’m not gonna hold that against you.

603
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:21,840
I won’t let you get to that.

604
00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:32,400
Tell me where you’d like a massage, sir.

605
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,200
I’m sore everywhere.

606
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:40,080
Especially over here on my shoulders.

607
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:40,760
Here?
That’s right.

608
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:42,360
This side, too.
Here, too?

609
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:44,520
Right.

610
00:39:44,800 --> 00:39:46,920
It hurts so much it shoots
right up my head.

611
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:48,280
It does?

612
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:49,760
My head hurts.

613
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:52,200
Aw, that’s nice.

614
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:54,160
My cheek also hurts now.

615
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:55,360
Must be the migraine.

616
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:56,520
Your cheek, huh?
That’s right.

617
00:39:57,480 --> 00:39:58,200
Here?

618
00:39:58,520 --> 00:39:59,240
Aw!

619
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:01,760
My lips also kinda…

620
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:03,040
Your lips?
Yes.

621
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:09,200
What about you? Does it hurt anywhere?

622
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:11,960
Here.

623
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:23,440
I love you, U.

624
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:25,440
I love you, too, North.

625
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:59,040
We finally wrapped up our project.

626
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,360
I’ve been exhausted.

627
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:02,880
I’m working.
Sit properly.

628
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:09,360
So do I have to look for a new hire?

629
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:11,000
I’m not sure.

630
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:12,800
We’ll have to see after I talk to them.

631
00:41:13,200 --> 00:41:16,000
But if I really am leaving, I’ll make sure I
draft up something for a smooth transition.

632
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:20,000
Are you going back to being a mall owner?

633
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:23,840
We’ll have to see what
the board of directors thinks.

634
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:26,600
My trustworthiness was quite
heavily damaged.

635
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:28,880
Sorry.

636
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:34,280
But how will I see you after this?

637
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:37,080
I don’t think I can march up to your office.

638
00:41:37,720 --> 00:41:40,040
It doesn’t seem like your Grandpa
is going to forgive me any time soon.

639
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:43,000
Are you going to give up?

640
00:41:45,760 --> 00:41:46,400
No way.

641
00:41:46,800 --> 00:41:47,720
I won’t give up.

642
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:50,960
We’ll work something out.

643
00:41:51,840 --> 00:41:52,320
Alright?

644
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:56,040
Hey.

645
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:18,640
Whose love language is this now?

646
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:23,880
Come in.

647
00:42:26,280 --> 00:42:27,480
Your Grandpa is here.

648
00:42:27,480 --> 00:42:30,240
And welcome back, sir.

649
00:42:35,560 --> 00:42:36,520
Hello, Grandpa.

650
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,600
Did you get everything in order
at Pure’s bakery?

651
00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:46,360
I’ll help him out the best I can
in case I have to leave suddenly.

652
00:42:48,120 --> 00:42:49,640
I’ve made up my mind.

653
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:56,000
If it’s okay with you, I want you
to resume your former position.

654
00:42:59,040 --> 00:42:59,880
I’m happy to.

655
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:04,240
Is Aunt Kia alright with this decision?

656
00:43:05,320 --> 00:43:11,840
About that, I’ve been thinking your
Aunt Kia should take over my role.

657
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:17,480
It’s about time I retire.

658
00:43:18,480 --> 00:43:21,440
I just want to be home and
play with my grandchildren.

659
00:43:26,480 --> 00:43:30,520
You’ll have to keep a low profile
at work for now, though, Pai.

660
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:37,440
Once the board approves,
you can take your title back right away.

661
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:40,600
Thank you, Grandpa.

662
00:43:42,560 --> 00:43:44,600
How are North and U doing?

663
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:45,960
Not bad.

664
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:48,000
They’re getting better and better.

665
00:43:48,760 --> 00:43:52,000
They didn’t look so promising at first,
but they’re no quitters, either.

666
00:43:53,800 --> 00:43:56,080
I think North has become
so much more mature.

667
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:56,720
I agree.

668
00:43:59,760 --> 00:44:01,120
You’re more mature as well, Pai.

669
00:44:03,800 --> 00:44:06,800
Going through something like that,

670
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:10,040
the options were either to
grow as a person or death, Grandpa.

671
00:44:17,360 --> 00:44:18,480
How are things with Tim?

672
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:24,600
I’ve had my eye on you guys, of course.

673
00:44:25,280 --> 00:44:28,920
I know what’s been going on.

674
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:35,360
It is as you can see.

675
00:44:36,360 --> 00:44:37,480
Tim refuses to leave.

676
00:44:38,600 --> 00:44:42,680
Well, then, I have one request.

677
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:50,640
Do not love him just because you think
he is the only person who loves you.

678
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:55,400
If you want to give him a chance,
you have to know him through.

679
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:59,280
Who he is, where he’s from,
what sort of family he grew up in.

680
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:02,000
And I need to know these things, too.

681
00:45:03,680 --> 00:45:07,280
Does that mean you want
to know Tim better?

682
00:45:08,120 --> 00:45:09,960
Well, you wouldn’t leave him, would you?

683
00:45:10,720 --> 00:45:13,160
So just take him in where I can see you,
like North did.

684
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:17,280
Of course.

685
00:45:23,040 --> 00:45:23,560
Well…

686
00:45:24,840 --> 00:45:25,640
Do you like them?

687
00:45:28,200 --> 00:45:29,160
The photos.

688
00:45:33,280 --> 00:45:34,600
I love them, Grandpa.

689
00:46:06,840 --> 00:46:09,320
Don’t hit that one, North.

690
00:46:09,640 --> 00:46:10,720
Here. Spin this.

691
00:46:10,720 --> 00:46:11,480
What if I just do this?

692
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:14,320
North, do it here first.

693
00:46:14,720 --> 00:46:16,600
- Here?
- The blue one.

694
00:46:17,040 --> 00:46:17,800
Your turn.

695
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:19,280
There.

696
00:46:19,280 --> 00:46:20,760
U, that’s the wrong side.

697
00:46:21,360 --> 00:46:22,680
Why don’t you two go back
and play at your home?

698
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:24,000
Don’t worry about leaving me alone.

699
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:26,000
I’m beginning to miss my solitude, actually.

700
00:46:28,960 --> 00:46:31,120
Where do I hammer
if I want the orange parts?

701
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:32,440
Here or here?

702
00:46:38,360 --> 00:46:39,440
Hmm…

703
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:41,920
Could be your personal chef.

704
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:42,960
Why don’t you go get him?

705
00:46:44,080 --> 00:46:45,080
And you acted like you didn’t hear me
when I told you to go.

706
00:46:57,080 --> 00:46:59,480
Was it a good day or a bad day?

707
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:03,520
Bad day.

708
00:47:04,680 --> 00:47:05,160
Alright.

709
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:06,440
Bad day, it is.

710
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:12,640
Hey, North.

711
00:47:16,920 --> 00:47:17,880
What are you making today?

712
00:47:18,600 --> 00:47:19,000
Steak.

713
00:47:19,840 --> 00:47:20,760
Why don’t you sit back and relax?

714
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:25,760
This is dangerous, Pai.

715
00:47:25,760 --> 00:47:27,760
No, the red part is here and
there are two blue pieces.

716
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:28,400
This is ice, you know.

717
00:47:29,920 --> 00:47:33,840
Can you break the ice, Pai?

718
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:35,920
Food is here.

719
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:38,000
This is for you, North.

720
00:47:38,320 --> 00:47:38,960
Thank you.

721
00:47:40,160 --> 00:47:40,760
Thank you, Tim.

722
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:55,720
Stop it.

723
00:47:58,880 --> 00:47:59,920
Alright.

724
00:48:12,960 --> 00:48:15,040
If you had a friend like that,
I’d die of jealousy.

725
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:15,840
Pai!

726
00:48:18,200 --> 00:48:19,680
I never stopped loving you, Tim.

727
00:48:20,160 --> 00:48:21,800
But when I think I have to trust you again,

728
00:48:22,320 --> 00:48:23,600
I can’t help but get so scared.

729
00:48:24,520 --> 00:48:28,160
Can we really marry
the same person twice?

730
00:48:32,680 --> 00:48:35,600
He still has much to prove.

731
00:48:35,720 --> 00:48:37,880
I’m more than willing to
spend my whole life doing it.

